1064
00:36:06,446 --> 00:36:08,546
I avoided. I mean, I stepped back a little.

1065
00:36:08,716 --> 00:36:11,646
But my opponent could tell I was in pain.

1066
00:36:12,016 --> 00:36:14,256
He kept following me and punching me right here.

1067
00:36:14,356 --> 00:36:15,855
(His weakness was spotted from the start.)

1068
00:36:15,856 --> 00:36:17,155
He spotted your weakness.

1069
00:36:17,156 --> 00:36:18,426
- It was so cruel. - Right.

1070
00:36:18,486 --> 00:36:19,686
He kept punching me right here on the same spot.

1071
00:36:19,826 --> 00:36:22,255
Even when he moved his body slightly,

1072
00:36:22,256 --> 00:36:23,556
I ended up doing this.

1073
00:36:23,966 --> 00:36:25,525
- It was my protective instinct. - You get startled.

1074
00:36:25,526 --> 00:36:28,936
- I kept blocking here. - Gosh. Right.

1075
00:36:29,296 --> 00:36:32,266
But he also caught me defending here.

1076
00:36:32,606 --> 00:36:34,205
Then he started attacking me here.

1077
00:36:34,206 --> 00:36:36,276
- He started kicking me here. - Right.

1078
00:36:37,176 --> 00:36:38,476
It hurt so much. Even more painful.

1079
00:36:38,806 --> 00:36:39,975
What happened to your adrenaline?

1080
00:36:39,976 --> 00:36:42,676
My adrenaline was gone. I didn't know where it was.

1081
00:36:42,776 --> 00:36:44,845
- When does it come out? - Where is your adrenaline?

1082
00:36:44,846 --> 00:36:46,985
You didn't get a chance to punch, Seung Yoon?

1083
00:36:46,986 --> 00:36:49,255
- On the second round, - He got a chance.

1084
00:36:49,256 --> 00:36:51,526
I got a chance. I grabbed one of his legs.

1085
00:36:51,986 --> 00:36:53,326
I turned him sideways.

1086
00:36:53,526 --> 00:36:54,725
- And he fell down. - Gosh.

1087
00:36:54,726 --> 00:36:57,726
When I finally knocked him down after being attacked all along,

1088
