1245
00:42:26,256 --> 00:42:27,495
- We have many. - We have many of them here.

1246
00:42:27,496 --> 00:42:28,596
I have one chance to do this, right?

1247
00:42:29,256 --> 00:42:30,356
"One chance?"

1248
00:42:30,826 --> 00:42:31,925
He asked if he had only one chance.

1249
00:42:31,926 --> 00:42:33,696
Gosh. He's such a funny character.

1250
00:42:33,996 --> 00:42:35,465
- That's it. - That's it.

1251
00:42:35,466 --> 00:42:36,666
("My Childhood Dream" by Turbo)

1252
00:42:37,566 --> 00:42:40,266
(It quickly turns into Turbo's concert.)

1253
00:42:42,676 --> 00:42:43,676
- Gosh. - Gosh.

1254
00:42:44,246 --> 00:42:47,415
- That's it. - He's good.

1255
00:42:47,416 --> 00:42:49,516
He memorized it.

1256
00:42:50,376 --> 00:42:51,485
("Black Cat" by Turbo)

1257
00:42:51,486 --> 00:42:52,885
- Gosh. - That's it.

1258
00:42:52,910 --> 00:42:54,110
- That's it. - Jump.

1259
00:42:54,986 --> 00:42:56,015
(Are you watching, Jong Kook?)

1260
00:42:56,016 --> 00:42:57,256
That's it.

1261
00:42:57,826 --> 00:42:59,485
- That's it. - Look at him.

1262
00:42:59,486 --> 00:43:00,726
- Gosh! - His dance is...

1263
00:43:01,356 --> 00:43:03,196
He looks tired.

1264
00:43:03,356 --> 00:43:05,266
- He practiced hard. - He looks tired.

1265
00:43:05,726 --> 00:43:07,635
- He's good. - That must be a good workout.

1266
00:43:07,636 --> 00:43:08,765
(Resting for a beat)

1267
00:43:08,766 --> 00:43:09,896
That's it.

1268
00:43:11,306 --> 00:43:12,705
(Black cat)

1269
00:43:12,706 --> 00:43:14,436
(Roaring)

1270
00:43:14,706 --> 00:43:17,206
(The cat is bulking up.)

1271
00:43:19,776 --> 00:43:20,816
(Roaring)

1272
00:43:23,746 --> 00:43:27,316
(Today is for the upper body workouts.)

1273
00:43:28,956 --> 00:43:31,386
(Today's workout is done.)

1274
00:43:31,756 --> 00:43:33,225
(They could feel his energy.)

1275
00:43:33,226 --> 00:43:35,055
- He's good. - He's good.

1276
00:43:35,056 --> 00:43:36,495
His body is used to dancing.

1277
00:43:36,496 --> 00:43:38,595
- Yes. - It is.

1278
00:43:38,596 --> 00:43:40,225
I was so shocked to see how good he was.

1279
00:43:40,226 --> 00:43:41,396
I know. I was so shocked.

1280
00:43:41,536 --> 00:43:42,965
I thought he was trying to be funny,

1281
00:43:42,966 --> 00:43:45,265
but Shin Dong and I could tell that he was a good dancer.

1282
00:43:45,266 --> 00:43:46,505
- He is. - Yes.

1283
00:43:46,506 --> 00:43:48,206
- He's flexible. - That's why he tried to learn.

1284
00:43:48,376 --> 00:43:50,536
- I went right away. - Yes.

1285
00:43:50,876 --> 00:43:52,805
After Sun Ho,

1286
00:43:52,806 --> 00:43:54,075
- it's Eun Bi's turn. - Eun Bi.

1287
00:43:54,076 --> 00:43:55,445
- Eun Bi is... - Me, finally?

1288
00:43:55,446 --> 00:43:57,615
You tried to match the related word.

1289
00:43:57,616 --> 00:43:58,715
- With that? - Does she have muscles?

1290
00:43:58,716 --> 00:44:00,515
You wrote, "I need durability against blows."

1291
00:44:00,516 --> 00:44:01,615
Weren't you the Water Queen?

1292
00:44:01,616 --> 00:44:03,055
- Why is that? - Water Queen.

1293
00:44:03,056 --> 00:44:05,656
- I recently went to the Himalayas. - Really?

1294
00:44:06,356 --> 00:44:09,396
- With Hong Chul? - Yes, with Hong Chul and Si Young.

1295
00:44:09,696 --> 00:44:11,095
It was spontaneous.

1296
00:44:11,096 --> 00:44:12,595
We were having dinner together,

1297
00:44:12,596 --> 00:44:13,995
and we said we should go to the Himalayas,

1298
00:44:13,996 --> 00:44:15,666
and that's why we went.

1299
00:44:15,766 --> 00:44:17,395
- Do you usually like hiking? - You don't look too fit.

1300
00:44:17,396 --> 00:44:19,835
It was my first time since middle school,

1301
00:44:19,836 --> 00:44:21,575
and the first place I went was the Himalayas.

1302
00:44:21,576 --> 00:44:23,236
- Goodness. - That's so high.

1303
00:44:23,376 --> 00:44:25,175
How far did you get?

1304
00:44:25,176 --> 00:44:27,005
It was 4,985m,

1305
00:44:27,006 --> 00:44:28,815
- so it was about 5,000m. - Really?

1306
00:44:28,816 --> 00:44:30,415
- Is that up to the base camp? - Gosh.

1307
00:44:30,416 --> 00:44:32,215
- No. - It starts from 2,000m.

1308
00:44:32,216 --> 00:44:33,415
That's how it is.

1309
00:44:33,416 --> 00:44:34,716
(From Kathmandu to Tsergo Ri)

1310
00:44:35,156 --> 00:44:39,026
(In order to get to Tsergo Ri, which is 5,000m above sea level)

1311
00:44:41,526 --> 00:44:44,966
(Their three-day adventure started!)

1312
00:44:45,066 --> 00:44:47,165
We slept in lodges in between,

1313
00:44:47,166 --> 00:44:49,195
- and we climbed for three days. - Really?

1314
00:44:49,196 --> 00:44:50,265
- Eun Bi. - Wasn't it hard?

1315
00:44:50,266 --> 00:44:51,735
Korean people get altitude sickness...

1316
00:44:51,736 --> 00:44:53,135
when they go over 3,000m above sea level.

1317
00:44:53,136 --> 00:44:54,175
That's right.

1318
00:44:54,176 --> 00:44:57,036
I started taking medication even before leaving Korea.

1319
00:44:57,506 --> 00:45:00,075
I kept taking them, even though it felt like...

1320
00:45:00,076 --> 00:45:01,275
I was overdoing it,

1321
00:45:01,276 --> 00:45:02,975
but it was so bad...

1322
00:45:02,976 --> 00:45:04,745
that my nose bled every morning.

1323
00:45:04,746 --> 00:45:06,045
- Really? - That's right.

1324
00:45:06,046 --> 00:45:07,245
Even when you didn't get hit, like Seung Yoon did?

1325
00:45:07,246 --> 00:45:09,616
No. I would just get nosebleeds in the morning.

1326
00:45:09,816 --> 00:45:11,625
Hong Chul had to stop in the middle...

1327
00:45:11,626 --> 00:45:13,986
because of altitude sickness, and he didn't make it to the top.

1328
00:45:14,356 --> 00:45:20,226
(Hong Chul didn't feel good because of altitude sickness.)

1329
00:45:20,626 --> 00:45:24,536
(He had to drop out and ride a horse back down.)

1330
00:45:24,836 --> 00:45:26,205
It really could be dangerous.

1331
00:45:26,206 --> 00:45:28,335
- It really is dangerous. - They even throw up.

1332
00:45:28,336 --> 00:45:31,445
You can't shower for several days when you go there.

1333
00:45:31,446 --> 00:45:33,075
Jang Hoon won't make it because of that.

1334
00:45:33,076 --> 00:45:34,946
- You're not allowed to shower. - Why?

1335
00:45:35,276 --> 00:45:37,175
Due to the lack of oxygen...

1336
00:45:37,176 --> 00:45:38,416
and because it's cold.

1337
00:45:38,616 --> 00:45:41,086
- If you wash, you really could... - Do you freeze?

1338
00:45:41,456 --> 00:45:42,515
- Temperature differences? - In extreme cases,

1339
00:45:42,516 --> 00:45:43,585
there are people who die.

1340
00:45:43,586 --> 00:45:45,825
- Because they wash? - You're never allowed to wash.

1341
00:45:45,826 --> 00:45:47,255
- To maintain the body temperature. - And you need to keep...

1342
00:45:47,256 --> 00:45:48,695
a beanie on when you sleep.

1343
00:45:48,696 --> 00:45:50,255
- The higher you get. - To keep you warm.

1344
00:45:50,256 --> 00:45:52,396
- To prevent the heat from escaping? - Yes.

1345
00:45:52,526 --> 00:45:53,765
Can you brush your teeth?

1346
00:45:53,766 --> 00:45:55,165
You can brush your teeth,

1347
00:45:55,166 --> 00:45:57,196
- but there's no hot water. - Sure.

1348
00:45:57,266 --> 00:46:00,365
- You boil about a liter of water, - Ice?

1349
00:46:00,366 --> 00:46:02,175
sleep with it,

1350
00:46:02,176 --> 00:46:04,175
and in the morning, when it gets lukewarm,

1351
00:46:04,176 --> 00:46:06,045
you wash your face, brush your teeth,

1352
00:46:06,046 --> 00:46:07,715
- and lightly wash up, - What did you eat there?

1353
00:46:07,716 --> 00:46:08,746
- and keep going. - The food.

1354
00:46:08,876 --> 00:46:11,785
There, we had local food and ramyeon.

1355
00:46:11,786 --> 00:46:13,415
- Even when you're hiking? - Yes.

1356
00:46:13,416 --> 00:46:14,885
The higher you get,

1357
00:46:14,886 --> 00:46:17,626
the price for soft drinks goes up as well.

1358
00:46:17,756 --> 00:46:19,555
- Really? - Even if it's the same...

1359
00:46:19,556 --> 00:46:21,155
- kind of soft drinks, - Sure.

1360
00:46:21,156 --> 00:46:22,826
- it gets more expensive, - Do they still have it, though?

1361
00:46:22,896 --> 00:46:24,666
How hard was it?

1362
00:46:24,826 --> 00:46:26,625
As I was going up,

1363
00:46:26,626 --> 00:46:28,235
up until we arrived at the top,

1364
00:46:28,236 --> 00:46:29,735
I really thought I could die.

1365
00:46:29,736 --> 00:46:30,866
- Gosh. - Really?

1366
00:46:31,006 --> 00:46:32,135
- It was really so tough. - Sure.

1367
00:46:32,136 --> 00:46:35,336
It was a type of pain and difficulty I had never experienced before.

1368
00:46:35,576 --> 00:46:38,406
I had always thought the toughest time in my life...

1369
00:46:38,546 --> 00:46:40,775
- was during the TV audition show. - It's the toughest.

1370
00:46:40,776 --> 00:46:41,945
- It's tough. - I thought it would be...

1371
00:46:41,946 --> 00:46:44,115
the hardest time in my life,

1372
00:46:44,116 --> 00:46:46,445
but I realized I could do it ten more times.

1373
00:46:46,446 --> 00:46:47,785
- Really? - That's how hard it was.

1374
00:46:47,786 --> 00:46:49,385
It was a type of pain I had never experienced...

1375
00:46:49,386 --> 00:46:50,785
- as a human being. - Really?

1376
00:46:50,786 --> 00:46:52,425
Climbing the Himalayas was ten times harder?

1377
00:46:52,426 --> 00:46:55,655
(She suddenly had to go and climb the Himalayas.)

1378
00:46:55,656 --> 00:46:59,366
(Eun Bi)

1379
00:47:00,066 --> 00:47:03,066
(Even during the extreme situations,)

1380
00:47:03,736 --> 00:47:06,265
(the beautiful landscape she faced felt like a present.)

1381
00:47:06,266 --> 00:47:10,576
(Photos taken by Eun Bi)

1382
00:47:10,636 --> 00:47:14,945
(Eun Bi)

1383
00:47:14,946 --> 00:47:16,645
As soon as I got to the top,

1384
00:47:16,646 --> 00:47:18,185
I didn't even imagine that I would cry,

1385
00:47:18,186 --> 00:47:20,115
but the tears came down.

1386
00:47:20,116 --> 00:47:21,556
That's amazing.

1387
00:47:25,156 --> 00:47:28,455
(I arrived...)

1388
00:47:28,456 --> 00:47:30,026
(without getting hurt.)

1389
00:47:30,296 --> 00:47:34,166
(I am thankful that I am alive.)

1390
00:47:34,536 --> 00:47:37,295
I wondered when I would ever get a chance...

1391
00:47:37,296 --> 00:47:38,805
- like this again. - That's amazing.

1392
00:47:38,806 --> 00:47:40,536
Basically,

1393
00:47:40,936 --> 00:47:43,835
you were born with the physical strength.

1394
00:47:43,836 --> 00:47:46,745
Because it's not possible for a novice...

1395
00:47:46,746 --> 00:47:48,845
- to climb the Himalayas... - Sure.

1396
00:47:48,846 --> 00:47:50,575
- up to 5,000m. - It's impossible.

1397
00:47:50,576 --> 00:47:52,715
I really didn't think I would make it, either.

1398
00:47:52,716 --> 00:47:55,516
- I went to the Himalayas as well. - What?

1399
00:47:56,116 --> 00:47:57,655
- With Um Hong Gil. - Yes.

1400
00:47:57,656 --> 00:47:58,685
(Ho Dong went for an interview with him.)

1401
00:47:58,686 --> 00:48:00,185
We went for a shoot.

1402
00:48:00,186 --> 00:48:02,295
Even then, the interview took place...

1403
00:48:02,296 --> 00:48:05,425
2,000m or 3,000m above sea level.

1404
00:48:05,426 --> 00:48:08,195
- It starts at 2,000m to 3,000m. - It starts like that.

1405
00:48:08,196 --> 00:48:11,165
I felt out of breath just thinking of the height.

1406
00:48:11,166 --> 00:48:13,265
- I know. - There's less oxygen.

1407
00:48:13,266 --> 00:48:15,235
You should never go with someone that you're comfortable with.

1408
00:48:15,236 --> 00:48:16,675
- Really? - What does that mean?

1409
00:48:16,676 --> 00:48:19,305
- Someone uncomfortable? - I went with a senior,

1410
00:48:19,306 --> 00:48:23,315
and I had to pay respect to them,

1411
00:48:23,316 --> 00:48:26,646
so I felt like I shouldn't be a nuisance.

1412
00:48:26,686 --> 00:48:29,255
- That could be. - So I felt more responsible.

1413
00:48:29,256 --> 00:48:31,085
- Yes. - "I have to keep going."

1414
00:48:31,086 --> 00:48:33,085
I had to go since they were going.

1415
00:48:33,086 --> 00:48:34,086
- Sure. - Wait.

1416
00:48:34,087 --> 00:48:37,226
Eun Bi, you're not going to show us your durability here, are you?

1417
00:48:37,596 --> 00:48:39,125
- Well... - I'm sure she has something else.

1418
00:48:39,126 --> 00:48:41,966
- Is there something to show us? - Oh, right.

1419
00:48:42,066 --> 00:48:43,895
I have an album coming.

1420
00:48:43,896 --> 00:48:46,066
- Come on. - I knew it.

1421
00:48:46,206 --> 00:48:48,305
You were saying that just to tell us about your album?

1422
00:48:48,306 --> 00:48:50,805
Did you pretend to be strong just because of your album?

1423
00:48:50,806 --> 00:48:52,806
I didn't know that I would be a part of this, either.

1424
00:48:53,176 --> 00:48:54,275
Really?

1425
00:48:54,276 --> 00:48:56,145
(I'm the only one different here.)

1426
00:48:56,146 --> 00:48:58,415
The dance performance...

1427
00:48:58,416 --> 00:49:00,345
requires a lot of stamina this time.

1428
00:49:00,346 --> 00:49:01,885
- Let's go. - Okay.

1429
00:49:01,886 --> 00:49:03,616
(Show us your new song!)

1430
00:49:03,756 --> 00:49:05,726
- Are you ready, Eun Bi? - Yes.

1431
00:49:06,456 --> 00:49:08,596
("Hello Stranger" by Kwon Eun Bi)

1432
00:49:11,266 --> 00:49:12,525
- Gosh. - Gosh.

1433
00:49:12,526 --> 00:49:15,096
- Gosh. - How amazing.

1434
00:49:15,266 --> 00:49:16,295
She's good.

1435
00:49:16,296 --> 00:49:18,236
- Look at her. - That's amazing.

1436
00:49:18,366 --> 00:49:19,736
- She's so good. - Gosh.

1437
00:49:21,776 --> 00:49:23,036
Gosh.

1438
00:49:27,376 --> 00:49:29,216
- She's so good at keeping balance. - Yes.

1439
00:49:30,076 --> 00:49:31,786
- Gosh. - She's one with the dance.

1440
00:49:35,456 --> 00:49:37,056
- That's good. - She's like this.

1441
00:49:42,356 --> 00:49:43,795
- Gosh. - That was so cool.

1442
00:49:43,796 --> 00:49:45,796
That must be so hard.

1443
00:49:46,766 --> 00:49:49,295
Make sure to do the dance, you guys.

1444
00:49:49,296 --> 00:49:51,235
What's the title?

1445
00:49:51,236 --> 00:49:52,935
- "Hello Stranger." - Is that why?

1446
00:49:52,936 --> 00:49:55,776
- Hello. - "Hello Stranger."

1447
00:49:55,806 --> 00:49:58,045
Now, moving on from Eun Bi.

1448
00:49:58,046 --> 00:50:00,076
The next is Seung Yoon.

1449
00:50:00,306 --> 00:50:02,045
"Natural Person"

1450
00:50:02,046 --> 00:50:03,215
- "I Am a Natural Person?" - Yes.

1451
00:50:03,216 --> 00:50:04,915
- "I Am a Natural Person." - That's so famous.

1452
00:50:04,916 --> 00:50:06,586
I heard the pay for re-runs is immense.

1453
00:50:06,686 --> 00:50:08,716
- They do so many re-runs. - Yes.

1454
00:50:08,786 --> 00:50:10,185
It's my mom's favorite show.

1455
00:50:10,186 --> 00:50:12,725
I hear that it has the most re-runs...

1456
00:50:12,726 --> 00:50:14,156
among local shows.

1457
00:50:14,186 --> 00:50:16,225
They did research last year,

1458
00:50:16,226 --> 00:50:18,196
and they had 400 re-runs a week.

1459
00:50:18,366 --> 00:50:19,825
I'm on television 400 times a week.

1460
00:50:19,826 --> 00:50:21,126
- Where do they show that? - Yes.

1461
00:50:21,296 --> 00:50:23,436
- For re-runs? - They have 400 re-runs.

1462
00:50:23,536 --> 00:50:24,935
- It's on... - It's true.

1463
00:50:24,936 --> 00:50:26,905
- It was an actual research. - many different channels.

1464
00:50:26,906 --> 00:50:28,575
- For the elders, - They love it.

1465
00:50:28,576 --> 00:50:30,836
they always see me in the mountains,

1466
00:50:30,976 --> 00:50:32,206
so they think I live in the wild.

1467
00:50:32,506 --> 00:50:34,045
- That's possible. - That's what they think.

1468
00:50:34,046 --> 00:50:35,915
Since they always see me in the mountains.

1469
00:50:35,916 --> 00:50:38,886
If you see some natural people, there are those who take pride.

1470
00:50:39,346 --> 00:50:41,585
They think that they are good at hiking.

1471
00:50:41,586 --> 00:50:43,516
- So they want to show us. - Yes.

1472
00:50:43,856 --> 00:50:46,225
There are some people who overdo things...

1473
00:50:46,226 --> 00:50:47,686
as they hike.

1474
00:50:47,996 --> 00:50:49,395
"Watch carefully."

1475
00:50:49,396 --> 00:50:51,765
"I can go this much."

1476
00:50:51,766 --> 00:50:53,065
And they keep taking us...

1477
00:50:53,066 --> 00:50:54,365
- to places. - That's hard.

1478
00:50:54,366 --> 00:50:56,095
If we meet someone like that, it's really hard.

1479
00:50:56,096 --> 00:50:58,736
But when they see that we're tired, they feel proud.

1480
00:50:58,836 --> 00:51:01,066
Once, the man kept going,

1481
00:51:01,206 --> 00:51:02,776
and it felt like he was lost.

1482
00:51:03,906 --> 00:51:05,746
He took you to places he had never gone to before.

1483
00:51:05,906 --> 00:51:08,375
- He didn't say so, - He was bad with directions.

1484
00:51:08,376 --> 00:51:09,376
You would have hiked as much as you would hike...

1485
00:51:09,377 --> 00:51:10,415
- the Himalayas. - The mountain...

1486
00:51:10,416 --> 00:51:13,185
- I think I hiked... - He was bad with directions.

1487
00:51:13,186 --> 00:51:14,585
I hiked as much as I would hike...

1488
00:51:14,586 --> 00:51:15,956
- the Himalayas. So, - Yes.

1489
00:51:16,216 --> 00:51:17,855
it felt like we had been there, but we went there again...

1490
00:51:17,856 --> 00:51:20,125
- and again. We circled around. - Right.

1491
00:51:20,126 --> 00:51:22,425
But he said, "How is it?"

1492
00:51:22,426 --> 00:51:23,596
"Is it doable now?"

1493
00:51:24,156 --> 00:51:26,325
- He turned around, - He pretended to be calm.

1494
00:51:26,326 --> 00:51:27,495
but he looked flustered.

1495
00:51:27,496 --> 00:51:30,265
He turned around but his eyes were shaking.

1496
00:51:30,266 --> 00:51:31,605
I had an instinctive feeling.

1497
00:51:31,606 --> 00:51:32,665
- "We're lost." - "We're lost."

1498
00:51:32,666 --> 00:51:33,735
- "We're lost." - "We're in trouble."

1499
00:51:33,736 --> 00:51:35,335
But he kept moving around.

1500
00:51:35,336 --> 00:51:37,575
Then, the sun started to set. This happens in the mountains.

1501
00:51:37,576 --> 00:51:38,775
When the sun sets, it turns dark very suddenly.

1502
00:51:38,776 --> 00:51:39,845
- It sets quickly. - That's scary.

1503
00:51:39,846 --> 00:51:41,615
- It suddenly becomes dark. - But as we went on,

1504
00:51:41,616 --> 00:51:43,115
- the sun set. - Goodness.

1505
00:51:43,116 --> 00:51:44,445
- What did you do? - So,

1506
00:51:44,446 --> 00:51:47,716
I think he also gave up. At the end, he said,

1507
00:51:47,986 --> 00:51:51,285
"Goodness. I don't know the way."

1508
00:51:51,286 --> 00:51:52,655
- Really? - He said that.

1509
00:51:52,656 --> 00:51:53,925
It was a crisis.

1510
00:51:53,926 --> 00:51:55,756
- It was a dangerous situation. - Right.

1511
00:51:56,156 --> 00:51:58,265
What could we do? We couldn't go down the mountain.

1512
00:51:58,266 --> 00:52:01,995
We hiked halfway up the mountain for 5 to 6 hours.

1513
00:52:01,996 --> 00:52:02,996
We were out of food...

1514
00:52:02,997 --> 00:52:04,165
- and water. - Goodness.

1515
00:52:04,166 --> 00:52:06,705
- It also started to rain. - That's bad.

1516
00:52:06,706 --> 00:52:09,375
We couldn't do anything. We had to stay the night, though.

1517
00:52:09,376 --> 00:52:10,706
There were no caves, either.

1518
00:52:11,346 --> 00:52:14,475
But there was a rock that looked like this,

1519
00:52:14,476 --> 00:52:16,315
and there were leaves underneath it.

1520
00:52:16,316 --> 00:52:19,015
So we all went under it,

1521
00:52:19,016 --> 00:52:21,215
and he said we could sleep under the leaves.

1522
00:52:21,216 --> 00:52:23,115
He was flustered,

1523
00:52:23,116 --> 00:52:24,385
but he said this with a confident voice.

1524
00:52:24,386 --> 00:52:26,786
"Have you ever slept under the leaves?"

1525
00:52:27,156 --> 00:52:28,225
I said, "No, I haven't."

1526
00:52:28,226 --> 00:52:29,495
- It was his first time too. - He said it would be good to try.

1527
00:52:29,496 --> 00:52:30,725
- It was his first time too. - He said that until the end.

1528
00:52:30,726 --> 00:52:32,995
"It's my first time too."

1529
00:52:32,996 --> 00:52:34,125
He said we could sleep there.

1530
00:52:34,126 --> 00:52:36,865
The production crew had some sort of plastic sheet.

1531
00:52:36,866 --> 00:52:39,065
They set it up to take shelter from the rain.

1532
00:52:39,066 --> 00:52:41,065
We had no water, so the youngest member...

1533
00:52:41,066 --> 00:52:44,135
drank the rainwater that gathered on the plastic sheet.

1534
00:52:44,136 --> 00:52:46,575
We were wondering how we were going to sleep there,

1535
00:52:46,576 --> 00:52:48,015
but our bodies were too tired.

1536
00:52:48,016 --> 00:52:49,046
- Right. - So,

1537
00:52:49,246 --> 00:52:51,315
he kindly covered us with the leaves.

1538
00:52:51,316 --> 00:52:52,415
"Cover yourselves with these."

1539
00:52:52,416 --> 00:52:54,715
I think he felt sorry. I covered myself with the leaves,

1540
00:52:54,716 --> 00:52:56,056
said, "Goodnight,"

1541
00:52:56,356 --> 00:52:58,056
and closed my eyes.

1542
00:52:58,326 --> 00:52:59,885
When I opened my eyes again, it was morning.

1543
00:52:59,886 --> 00:53:01,695
- You slept so well? - You were tired.

1544
00:53:01,696 --> 00:53:04,095
I've never slept so well...

1545
00:53:04,096 --> 00:53:06,825
in my entire life.

1546
00:53:06,826 --> 00:53:08,435
I just closed my eyes...

1547
00:53:08,436 --> 00:53:10,395
and opened them when the birds chirped,

1548
00:53:10,396 --> 00:53:12,035
- and it was morning. - How many hours had passed?

1549
00:53:12,036 --> 00:53:15,075
The rain cleared off, and everything was bright.

1550
00:53:15,076 --> 00:53:17,575
I still can't forget that feeling.

1551
00:53:17,576 --> 00:53:20,345
So, thanks to that man who got lost,

1552
00:53:20,346 --> 00:53:22,675
I experienced true nature.

1553
00:53:22,676 --> 00:53:24,075
Where did that man sleep?

1554
00:53:24,076 --> 00:53:25,816
Didn't he go home in the middle of the night because it was cold?

1555
00:53:26,216 --> 00:53:27,615
He gave you all the leaves.

1556
00:53:27,616 --> 00:53:28,755
He...

1557
00:53:28,756 --> 00:53:30,285
- He slept at a hotel. - When I woke up,

1558
00:53:30,286 --> 00:53:31,725
- At a hotel. - he was next to me.

1559
00:53:31,726 --> 00:53:32,855
"A room for one person, please."

1560
00:53:32,856 --> 00:53:33,886
He was next to me.

1561
00:53:34,456 --> 00:53:35,456
- It would be funny... - He was next to me.

1562
00:53:35,457 --> 00:53:36,695
if he wasn't there when you woke up.

1563
00:53:36,696 --> 00:53:38,595
He was next to me.

1564
00:53:38,596 --> 00:53:42,065
In the morning, he said, "I got lost."

1565
00:53:42,066 --> 00:53:43,435
"I'm sorry."

1566
00:53:43,436 --> 00:53:45,305
We all said, "It was a good experience."

1567
00:53:45,306 --> 00:53:46,905
It ended well like that.

1568
00:53:46,906 --> 00:53:49,375
We considered it an event.

1569
00:53:49,376 --> 00:53:50,775
I'm curious.

1570
00:53:50,776 --> 00:53:52,275
When I watch "I Am a Natural Person,"

1571
00:53:52,276 --> 00:53:56,675
I get to learn that there are such places in Korea.

1572
00:53:56,676 --> 00:53:58,515
- How do you find them? - So,

1573
00:53:58,516 --> 00:54:00,815
in the early days,

1574
00:54:00,816 --> 00:54:04,386
the writers used to look at the satellite pictures.

1575
00:54:04,686 --> 00:54:06,085
This is what I heard.

1576
00:54:06,086 --> 00:54:07,325
When they look at satellite pictures,

1577
00:54:07,326 --> 00:54:08,655
there is a house...

1578
00:54:08,656 --> 00:54:09,955
- in the middle of the mountain, - They find a house?

1579
00:54:09,956 --> 00:54:12,165
and they go and explore the place.

1580
00:54:12,166 --> 00:54:14,765
I think many people went into the mountains...

1581
00:54:14,766 --> 00:54:17,065
because that show went on for so long.

1582
00:54:17,066 --> 00:54:19,005
Some people hate it.

1583
00:54:19,006 --> 00:54:20,335
- Why? - "What are you going to do?"

1584
00:54:20,336 --> 00:54:23,335
"My husband says he'll go into the mountain because of you."

1585
00:54:23,336 --> 00:54:24,745
"Do something about it!"

1586
00:54:24,746 --> 00:54:26,005
They used you as an excuse.

1587
00:54:26,006 --> 00:54:28,615
But there are people who like it for the same reason.

1588
00:54:28,616 --> 00:54:30,745
- "Thanks to you, my husband..." - She didn't want to see him.

1589
00:54:30,746 --> 00:54:32,445
"said he would go and live in the mountain."

1590
00:54:32,446 --> 00:54:34,045
"Please keep it up until he goes there."

1591
00:54:34,046 --> 00:54:35,255
- There are some people like that. - There are both sides.

1592
00:54:35,256 --> 00:54:36,455
"Please keep it up until he goes there."

1593
00:54:36,456 --> 00:54:38,355
Since the show has been going on for a long time,

1594
00:54:38,356 --> 00:54:39,725
- I think... - Has it been about 14 years?

1595
00:54:39,726 --> 00:54:41,385
This is the 14th year.

1596
00:54:41,386 --> 00:54:42,995
- That's amazing. - That's amazing.

1597
00:54:42,996 --> 00:54:44,625
- What is it? - Lastly, Min Ji.

1598
00:54:44,626 --> 00:54:45,696
Min Ji.

1599
00:54:47,466 --> 00:54:49,395
As the related word,

1600
00:54:49,396 --> 00:54:51,735
Min Ji wrote "Subway versus human."

1601
00:54:51,736 --> 00:54:53,205
- The one that got famous. - Subway?

1602
00:54:53,206 --> 00:54:54,875
Is it the one they did on "Infinite Challenge?"

1603
00:54:54,876 --> 00:54:56,805
- The running race? - Did you run next to the train?

1604
00:54:56,806 --> 00:54:58,775
I raced with a subway train.

1605
00:54:58,776 --> 00:54:59,776
- What? - You did?

1606
00:54:59,777 --> 00:55:00,975
I did.

1607
00:55:00,976 --> 00:55:02,075
On a variety show?

1608
00:55:02,076 --> 00:55:03,415
- On my YouTube channel. - On YouTube.

1609
00:55:03,416 --> 00:55:04,715
Really?

1610
00:55:04,716 --> 00:55:06,385
How can you race with it?

1611
00:55:06,386 --> 00:55:07,515
- Let's watch it. - Do you want to watch it?

1612
00:55:07,516 --> 00:55:08,555
How did you do it?

1613
00:55:08,556 --> 00:55:09,556
(The train slowly makes a stop.)

1614
00:55:09,786 --> 00:55:11,555
You got out and ran to the next station?

1615
00:55:11,556 --> 00:55:12,556
Yes.

1616
00:55:13,286 --> 00:55:14,355
What does that mean?

1617
00:55:14,356 --> 00:55:16,355
- She goes to the next station... - I got out of Dongdaemun Station...

1618
00:55:16,356 --> 00:55:17,795
- and gets on the subway. - and caught the subway again.

1619
00:55:17,796 --> 00:55:20,195
- But you're not going straight. - It's not the normal route.

1620
00:55:20,196 --> 00:55:21,795
- It would be harder. - Exactly.

1621
00:55:21,796 --> 00:55:23,065
That's right. It was my first time doing that.

1622
00:55:23,066 --> 00:55:24,736
- I didn't practice. - She will take the same train.

1623
00:55:25,366 --> 00:55:27,535
Dongmyo.

1624
00:55:27,536 --> 00:55:28,536
What is that?
(Min Ji enters the entrance.)

1625
00:55:29,537 --> 00:55:30,705
- What? - It's Dongmyo.

1626
00:55:30,706 --> 00:55:32,075
It's about 600m apart.

1627
00:55:32,076 --> 00:55:34,006
But it only took a bit more than one minute.

1628
00:55:34,406 --> 00:55:35,475
She has to enter,

1629
00:55:35,476 --> 00:55:36,715
- Exactly. - and there are people.

1630
00:55:36,716 --> 00:55:37,945
It's...

1631
00:55:37,946 --> 00:55:39,085
Is it there?

1632
00:55:39,086 --> 00:55:40,686
It's a tight schedule.

1633
00:55:43,156 --> 00:55:45,356
- It... - She succeeded.

1634
00:55:47,086 --> 00:55:48,155
- From Dongdaemun Station... - It takes 2 minutes 10 seconds...

1635
00:55:48,156 --> 00:55:49,225
from one station to the next.

1636
00:55:49,226 --> 00:55:50,395
- You caught it. - You can't even run...

1637
00:55:50,396 --> 00:55:51,595
- at full speed there. - Right.

1638
00:55:51,596 --> 00:55:53,065
There are many obstacles.

1639
00:55:53,066 --> 00:55:54,666
- Right. - That's right.

1640
00:55:54,766 --> 00:55:56,865
I tried it...

1641
00:55:56,866 --> 00:55:58,066
because of my pride.

1642
00:55:58,966 --> 00:56:01,305
I was worried because it was my first attempt.

1643
00:56:01,306 --> 00:56:02,875
- So I paced myself. - Yes.

1644
00:56:02,876 --> 00:56:04,605
But after I did it once,

1645
00:56:04,606 --> 00:56:07,005
I could do it 3 to 4 more times.

1646
00:56:07,006 --> 00:56:08,575
- You have an amazing stamina. - And...

1647
00:56:08,576 --> 00:56:10,315
- That's amazing. - later on, I got there earlier...

1648
00:56:10,316 --> 00:56:11,885
- and waited for the train. - Really?

1649
00:56:11,886 --> 00:56:12,886
Yes.

1650
00:56:12,887 --> 00:56:16,156
What was your best record for 100m during your school years?

1651
00:56:16,516 --> 00:56:18,525
- People ask you this a lot, right? - I think they would.

1652
00:56:18,526 --> 00:56:20,255
- I am curious, though. - Your 100m record.

1653
00:56:20,256 --> 00:56:22,755
- What's your 100m record? - It would be like the big 3.

1654
00:56:22,756 --> 00:56:26,925
My 100m record is a very old one.

1655
00:56:26,926 --> 00:56:29,135
I got annoyed...

1656
00:56:29,136 --> 00:56:30,295
- because people kept asking. - Yes.

1657
00:56:30,296 --> 00:56:31,495
- Why? - So I told my coach...

1658
00:56:31,496 --> 00:56:33,705
that I would run the next 100m race.

1659
00:56:33,706 --> 00:56:34,735
- The race? - So I do have...

1660
00:56:34,736 --> 00:56:36,305
one official record.

1661
00:56:36,306 --> 00:56:38,405
- What was it? - I went there without practicing,

1662
00:56:38,406 --> 00:56:40,276
so I'm not that satisfied. It was 12.50 seconds.

1663
00:56:40,776 --> 00:56:43,015
- It was 12.50 without practice? - It was 12.50 seconds?

1664
00:56:43,016 --> 00:56:44,885
The real 100m track is really long.

1665
00:56:44,886 --> 00:56:46,185
- It's longer than you think. - It's really long

1666
00:56:46,186 --> 00:56:47,785
- That's right. - The official record I had...

1667
00:56:47,786 --> 00:56:50,916
when I was a basketball player was 12.8 seconds.

1668
00:56:51,556 --> 00:56:52,685
That's because he just gets to the finish line...

1669
00:56:52,686 --> 00:56:54,086
when he falls down in the middle.

1670
00:56:54,456 --> 00:56:56,155
- When he was an athlete. - He could be in second place...

1671
00:56:56,156 --> 00:56:57,655
- and fall down to become the first. - It's like pushing your foot out...

1672
00:56:57,656 --> 00:56:59,496
in short-track speed skating.

1673
00:56:59,766 --> 00:57:00,865
That's how he finishes.

1674
00:57:00,866 --> 00:57:03,335
What's your 400m record, then?

1675
00:57:03,336 --> 00:57:05,765
- My best record is 56 seconds. - What?

1676
00:57:05,766 --> 00:57:07,365
- You run 400m within a minute? - I finish it in less than a minute.

1677
00:57:07,366 --> 00:57:08,435
- A lap. - Right.

1678
00:57:08,436 --> 00:57:09,575
- Is that possible? - It's like...

1679
00:57:09,576 --> 00:57:11,405
running 100m 4 times.

1680
00:57:11,406 --> 00:57:13,446
Were you good at running ever since you were young?

1681
00:57:14,076 --> 00:57:16,375
I wasn't so good when I was young.

1682
00:57:16,376 --> 00:57:17,945
When did you start running then?

1683
00:57:17,946 --> 00:57:20,085
I had a talent in sports when I was young.

1684
00:57:20,086 --> 00:57:21,955
Did you do other sports before doing track and field?

1685
00:57:21,956 --> 00:57:24,015
I did taekwondo for eight years.

1686
00:57:24,016 --> 00:57:26,385
- You liked sports. - I did both track and field...

1687
00:57:26,386 --> 00:57:28,625
and taekwondo.

1688
00:57:28,626 --> 00:57:31,225
I couldn't decide at the time.

1689
00:57:31,226 --> 00:57:32,895
- You couldn't? - Then, one day,

1690
00:57:32,896 --> 00:57:35,295
- One day. - I was going home.

1691
00:57:35,296 --> 00:57:37,736
On my way home, suddenly,

1692
00:57:38,536 --> 00:57:39,865
some high school girls and boys,

1693
00:57:39,866 --> 00:57:42,405
who were smoking,

1694
00:57:42,406 --> 00:57:43,435
Those punks.

1695
00:57:43,436 --> 00:57:47,246
said to me, "Come here for a minute."

1696
00:57:47,706 --> 00:57:49,815
Anyone could tell that they wanted to take money from me.

1697
00:57:49,816 --> 00:57:51,015
(It was clear that they called her with suspicious intentions.)

1698
00:57:51,016 --> 00:57:53,245
One girl asked, "I don't have my bus fare."

1699
00:57:53,246 --> 00:57:55,516
"Could you lend me some? Do you have money?"

1700
00:57:55,816 --> 00:57:56,985
I couldn't act,

1701
00:57:56,986 --> 00:57:58,355
and I was too honest.

1702
00:57:58,356 --> 00:58:01,326
- I was wearing a uniform even then. - Yes.

1703
00:58:02,056 --> 00:58:03,956
I had five dollars in my pocket.

1704
00:58:04,296 --> 00:58:05,696
I said, "No, I don't have."

1705
00:58:06,366 --> 00:58:07,795
- You held it. - I held...

1706
00:58:07,796 --> 00:58:09,165
my pocket.

1707
00:58:09,166 --> 00:58:10,965
I said, "No, I don't have."

1708
00:58:10,966 --> 00:58:12,535
But anyone could tell that I had money.

1709
00:58:12,536 --> 00:58:14,335
She got angry and threw away the cigarette...

1710
00:58:14,336 --> 00:58:15,576
and said, "Come here."

1711
00:58:16,106 --> 00:58:17,835
I checked their shoes.

1712
00:58:17,836 --> 00:58:19,045
"This girl is wearing sneakers."

1713
00:58:19,046 --> 00:58:20,505
"Those guys are wearing slippers."

1714
00:58:20,506 --> 00:58:22,646
- In that short time? - "I'm wearing slippers."

1715
00:58:23,076 --> 00:58:24,576
- You were wearing slippers? - I was wearing slippers.

1716
00:58:25,246 --> 00:58:27,686
When the girl came this close,

1717
00:58:27,986 --> 00:58:30,785
I just ran away.

1718
00:58:30,786 --> 00:58:31,925
- In your slippers? - Yes.

1719
00:58:31,926 --> 00:58:34,995
She said, "Get her!" and all the girls came running.

1720
00:58:34,996 --> 00:58:37,295
I ran as fast as I could.

1721
00:58:37,296 --> 00:58:40,295
Then I looked back,

1722
00:58:40,296 --> 00:58:42,365
and they were struggling to run from far behind.

1723
00:58:42,366 --> 00:58:44,735
I could still run further.

1724
00:58:44,736 --> 00:58:47,235
- That's how you got back. - But when they saw me stop,

1725
00:58:47,236 --> 00:58:48,775
they started running again.

1726
00:58:48,776 --> 00:58:50,735
I ran while crying...

1727
00:58:50,736 --> 00:58:52,505
and entered a supermarket.

1728
00:58:52,506 --> 00:58:54,905
"Please call the police."

1729
00:58:54,906 --> 00:58:56,175
"The high school students are chasing me."

1730
00:58:56,176 --> 00:58:57,445
"They want to take my money."

1731
00:58:57,446 --> 00:58:58,845
The man went out and checked.

1732
00:58:58,846 --> 00:59:01,216
He said, "They're gone. It's okay."

1733
00:59:01,516 --> 00:59:03,115
That's how you went to track and field.

1734
00:59:03,116 --> 00:59:04,215
- That's when you realized. - Taekwondo...

1735
00:59:04,216 --> 00:59:05,325
- Yes. - I should run.

1736
00:59:05,326 --> 00:59:07,025
- "I..." - "I should be..."

1737
00:59:07,026 --> 00:59:08,055
- "in running." - "I should be..."

1738
00:59:08,056 --> 00:59:09,425
- "in track and field." - Exactly.

1739
00:59:09,426 --> 00:59:12,925
- Athletes have good ankles. - Yes.

1740
00:59:12,926 --> 00:59:14,495
- That's right. - Were you born with them?

1741
00:59:14,496 --> 00:59:16,195
They're good at Sargent jumps.

1742
00:59:16,196 --> 00:59:18,765
- Jumping up? - Sargent.

1743
00:59:18,766 --> 00:59:21,205
- How many meters did you jump? - I didn't check the meters.

1744
00:59:21,206 --> 00:59:22,575
